                    <h1 class="fbcms_content fbcms_plaintext inside_title" id="content_47943">COVID-19 Resources and Announcements</h1>
                    <div class="fbcms_content fbcms_richtext inside_center" id="content_47950">
    <div class="fbcms_richtext_content">
        <p>4/21/2020</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Senior Class of 2020,</p>

<p>As we are working with student representatives and staff to plan virtual and potential in person events to honor your class, we also want to have a more immediate celebration as the graduating class of 2020!</p>

<p>On April 24, 2020, at 8:20 pm (Military time 20:20), the stadium lights will go on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds.  This will illuminate our newest painted logo on our varsity football field, in honor of the Class of 2020.  We know that you will want to share in this celebration, but please keep in mind that we want you to be safe.  Social distancing outside of the stadium, in cars, with protective gear would be the best way to participate.  Closer to the graduation date, we are also planning another lighted event, and having a drone fly over the stadium, and live streaming the recording for you as well! </p>

<p>Please know that we appreciate your strength and positivity at this challenging time.  We are hoping to have a timeline for more events by the end of next week, so stay tuned for more information, as we celebrate the Class of 2020!</p>

<p>Sincerely,</p>

<p>Dr. Mandy Stewart</p>

<p>Superintendent- Charlotte Public Schools</p>

<p> </p>

<p> </p>
